  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Mechanism | Add Pin-Joint</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Add Pin-Joint</para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-ServoGearboxTorqueSpeed">Edit-Pin-Joint</link> ( Motor and Gearbox Sizing )</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Terminologie</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="7" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:250px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box-Elements" style="text-align:right;">Revolute-Pair :</para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:450px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">a joint that allows only rotary motion between two rigid-bodies <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Parts</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:250px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Pin-Joint </text><text styleclass="Popup Box">(general definition)</text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements"> :</text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:450px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">a joint that uses a Pin to connect two rigid-bodies &#160;</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:250px;">
          <para styleclass="Element" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Pin-Joint </text><text styleclass="Popup Box">(MechDesigner definition)</text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements"> : </text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:450px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">a joint that forces a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text> in a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> to be coincident with a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text> in a different <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text>. The Parts </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:250px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point : </text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:450px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">a fixed position that is on the XY-Plane of a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text>. </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:250px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text><text styleclass="Popup Box"> (alternative definition)</text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:450px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text> represents an <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Axis</text> that is perpendicular to the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Popup Box2">Mechanism-Plane</text>. </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:250px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Pin-Joint </text><text styleclass="Popup Box">(alternative definition)</text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements"> : </text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:450px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="VariableName-small">joint</text> in which an <text styleclass="VariableName-small">axis</text> (defined by a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text>) in a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> is made to be a coincident with an <text styleclass="VariableName-small">axis</text> (defined by a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text>) in a different <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2" style="width:450px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2"><text styleclass="Popup Box">The XY-Plane of all Parts (and the Base-Part) in a Mechanism-Editor are coplanar with the Mechanism-Plane.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">What is a Pin-Joint</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text style="font-style:normal;">A</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Element">Pin-Joint: </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <text styleclass="Element">Parts</text> can only rotate relative to each other, with the <text styleclass="Element">Pin-Joint</text> as the rotating-axis. </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Usually, use a <text styleclass="Element">Pin-Joint</text> to model a rotary bearing.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">A Pin-Joint </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
